What you need to know:

The loss is a major set back to the bankers as the race towards the June 30 deadline when the name of the team at the top of the log will be submitted to Caf as the country's representative to the Champions League next season.Following KCB's loss, 13-time champions AFC Leopards can open a three-point lead at the helm of the league on Sunday if they beat newbies Bidco United at the same venue.Leopards are joint top with KCB on 36 points but have an inferior goal difference. KCB have now played 18 matches while Leopards have a game in hand.